Text:
*** WARNING ***
Contains virus "W32/Sdbot.worm.gen.bj" according to McAfee

*** WARNING *** #2
Symantec AntiVirus (SAV) finds "W32.IRCBot" in the keygen.exe

The pain in the ass is that the keygen DOES WORK.  I used it BEFORE I had SAV.  After a scan, SAV deleted the file and now I can't download the same keygen without SAV stomping it out of existence the moment it's downloaded.  Bummer.

Can someone please put here a serial for this app?
The keygen doesn't work with me. It says: "Windows cannot access the device, path or specified file. Perhaps you don't have the adequate permissions to access the item."
I am the system administrator.

Oops, it worked now! :)
It was my anti-virus - avast! - that was blocking from executing the file.
I disabled it and than the keygen worked.
PS: it looks that the trojan encountered in the keygen is harmless! ;)
